<title>Strange Maps, Julius Scissor and cycle thefts</title>
<description>&lt;p&gt;Have you discovered the &lt;a href=&quot;http://strangemaps.wordpress.com&quot;&gt;Strange Maps&lt;/a&gt; blog? It&amp;#8217;s consistently excellent but &lt;a href=&quot;http://strangemaps.wordpress.com/2009/02/01/358-huns-hair-salons-and-puns/&quot;&gt;this recent entry&lt;/a&gt;, which snips a very strange map from &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.zeit.de/&quot;&gt;Die Zeit&lt;/a&gt;, is a cut above the rest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://strangemaps.wordpress.com/2009/02/01/358-huns-hair-salons-and-puns/&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://strangemaps.files.wordpress.com/2009/02/friseur.jpg?w=600&amp;h=731&quot; width=&quot;600&quot; height=&quot;731&quot; alt=&quot;German hairdressers&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;continue-reading&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reading through the comments, I learn &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ziet.de&quot;&gt;Die Ziet&lt;/a&gt; has been running a series featuring &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.zeit.de/themen/leben/gesellschaft/deutschlandkarten/index-deutschlandkarten&quot;&gt;similarly imaginative cartographics&lt;/a&gt;. Here are the German &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.zeit.de/2008/40/Karte-40&quot;&gt;cycle theft hotspots&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.zeit.de/2008/40/Karte-40&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://zeus.zeit.de/bilder/2008/40/leben/zeit-magazin-leben/diebstahl-karte/diebstahl-karte-800.gif&quot; width=&quot;600&quot; height=&quot;822&quot; alt=&quot;Cycle theft in Germany&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
<dc:date>2009-02-02</dc:date>
<guid>http://tag.wordaligned.org/posts/strange-maps-julius-scissor-and-cycle-thefts</guid>
<author>tag@wordaligned.org (Thomas Guest)</author>
